<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="nomenclatural note">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Nomenclatural note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
The species epithet of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loes. &amp; Rehder in Sargent" authorityYear="1913" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Euonymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euonymus aquifolium" order="Celastrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Euonymus aquifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been changed to &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loes. &amp; Rehder" authorityYear="1913" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Euonymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euonymus aquifolius" order="Celastrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Euonymus aquifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; to agree with the generic gender based on the assumption that this epithet was used as adjectival in form, and this was generally followed (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Chang, CY" editor="Chang, CY" journalOrPublisher="4. Science and Technological Publishing House of Sichuan, Chengdu" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="247 - 346" refId="B3" refString="Chang, CY, 1988. Celastraceae. In: Chang, CY, Ed., Flora Sichuanica, vol. 4. Science and Technological Publishing House of Sichuan, Chengdu: 247 - 346" title="Celastraceae." volumeTitle="Flora Sichuanica, vol." year="1988">Chang 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cheng, CY" editor="Cheng, CY" journalOrPublisher="45 (3). Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="1 - 218" refId="B4" refString="Cheng, CY, Kao, TC, Ma, QS, Ma, JS, Huang, PH, 1999. Celastraceae. In: Cheng, CY, Huang, PH, Eds., Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae vol. 45(3). Science Press, Beijing: 1 - 218" title="Celastraceae." volumeTitle="Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae vol." year="1999">Cheng et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ma, JS" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="11. Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="439 - 492" refId="B20" refString="Ma, JS, Zhang, ZX, Liu, QR, Peng, H, Funston, M, 2008. Celastraceae. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Hong, DY, Eds., Flora of China, vol. 11. Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis: 439 - 492" title="Celastraceae." volumeTitle="Flora of China, vol." year="2008">Ma et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hou, J" journalOrPublisher="Central Party Literature Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" publicationUrl="https://www.ipni.org/" refId="B12" refString="2022. . https://www.ipni.org/" url="https://www.ipni.org/" year="2022">IPNI 2022</bibRefCitation>
). However, when it was originally proposed, the initial letter of the epithet was capitalized as &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P.Miller" authorityYear="1754" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="Aquifolium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aquifolium" order="Aquifoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Aquifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.191" author="Sargent, CS" journalOrPublisher="The University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B30" refString="Sargent, CS, 1911-1913. PlantaeWilsonianae. An enumeration of the woody plants collected in western China for the Arnold Arboretum of Harvard University during the years 1907, 1908, and 1910 by E. H. Wilson, vol. 1. The University Press, Cambridge, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.191" title="PlantaeWilsonianae. An enumeration of the woody plants collected in western China for the Arnold Arboretum of Harvard University during the years 1907, 1908, and 1910 by E. H. Wilson, vol. 1." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.191" year="1911 - 1913">Sargent 1913</bibRefCitation>
), and that was customary then to indicate the epithet was applied after a proper noun, such as a person or a genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Clifford, HT" journalOrPublisher="Springer, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B6" refString="Clifford, HT, Bostock, PD, 2007. Etymological Dictionary of Grass. Springer, Berlin" title="Etymological Dictionary of Grass." year="2007">Clifford and Bostock 2007</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P.Miller" authorityYear="1754" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="Aquifolium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aquifolium" order="Aquifoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Aquifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.79061" author="Miller, P" journalOrPublisher="Printed for the Author, London, without pagination" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B22" refString="Miller, P, 1754. The Gardeners Dictionary: containing the methods of cultivating and improving all sorts of trees, plants, and flowers, for......, vol. 1, 4th edn. Printed for the Author, London, without pagination, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.79061" title="The Gardeners Dictionary: containing the methods of cultivating and improving all sorts of trees, plants, and flowers, for ......, vol. 1, 4 th edn." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.79061" year="1754">Miller (1754)</bibRefCitation>
is an illegitimate superfluous generic name of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="Ilex" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ilex" order="Aquifoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Ilex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C" journalOrPublisher="Impensis Laurenti Salvii, Holmiae" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B18" refString="Linnaeus, C, 1753. Species Plantarum, vol. 1-2. Impensis Laurenti Salvii, Holmiae" title="Species Plantarum, vol. 1 - 2." year="1753">Linnaeus (1753)</bibRefCitation>
, though it could also be used as an adjective (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loes. &amp; Rehder" authorityYear="1913" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Euonymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euonymus aquifolius" order="Celastrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Euonymus aquifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Loesener &amp; Rehder also capitalized the epithet when describing other species in the same publication (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.191" author="Sargent, CS" journalOrPublisher="The University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B30" refString="Sargent, CS, 1911-1913. PlantaeWilsonianae. An enumeration of the woody plants collected in western China for the Arnold Arboretum of Harvard University during the years 1907, 1908, and 1910 by E. H. Wilson, vol. 1. The University Press, Cambridge, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.191" title="PlantaeWilsonianae. An enumeration of the woody plants collected in western China for the Arnold Arboretum of Harvard University during the years 1907, 1908, and 1910 by E. H. Wilson, vol. 1." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.191" year="1911 - 1913">Sargent 1913</bibRefCitation>
). For example: 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Euonymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euonymus sargentianus" order="Celastrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sargentianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Euonymus sargentianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Loes. &amp; Rehder in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.191" author="Sargent, CS" journalOrPublisher="The University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B30" refString="Sargent, CS, 1911-1913. PlantaeWilsonianae. An enumeration of the woody plants collected in western China for the Arnold Arboretum of Harvard University during the years 1907, 1908, and 1910 by E. H. Wilson, vol. 1. The University Press, Cambridge, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.191" title="PlantaeWilsonianae. An enumeration of the woody plants collected in western China for the Arnold Arboretum of Harvard University during the years 1907, 1908, and 1910 by E. H. Wilson, vol. 1." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.191" year="1911 - 1913">Sargent (1913)</bibRefCitation>
by naming the epithet as &quot; 
<taxonomicName genus="Sargentiana" lsidName="Sargentiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Sargentiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; (named after a person), and 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. oblongifolius" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="oblongifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">E. oblongifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Loes. &amp; Rehder in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.191" author="Sargent, CS" journalOrPublisher="The University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B30" refString="Sargent, CS, 1911-1913. PlantaeWilsonianae. An enumeration of the woody plants collected in western China for the Arnold Arboretum of Harvard University during the years 1907, 1908, and 1910 by E. H. Wilson, vol. 1. The University Press, Cambridge, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.191" title="PlantaeWilsonianae. An enumeration of the woody plants collected in western China for the Arnold Arboretum of Harvard University during the years 1907, 1908, and 1910 by E. H. Wilson, vol. 1." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.191" year="1911 - 1913">Sargent (1913)</bibRefCitation>
as &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">oblongifolia</emphasis>
&quot;. This conclusion is further supported based on a review of the handwriting annotations by those authors on the type material of these taxa, where the species epithets of 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. aquifolium" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="aquifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">E. aquifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">E. H. Wilson 1366</emphasis>
, A) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
E. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Euonymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euonymus sargentianus" order="Celastrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sargentianus">Euonymus sargentianus</taxonomicName>
(E. H. Wilson 1187
</emphasis>
, A) were written in uppercase, while that of 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. oblongifolius" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" rank="species" species="oblongifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">E. oblongifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">E. H. Wilson 3125</emphasis>
, A) was in lowercase. Therefore, the species epithet of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loes. &amp; Rehder in Sargent" authorityYear="1913" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Euonymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euonymus aquifolium" order="Celastrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Euonymus aquifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should retain its own gender and termination according to Art. 23.5 of ICN (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B37" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, WH, Li, DZ, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="rarity and conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Rarity and conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
The type material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loes. &amp; Rehder in Sargent" authorityYear="1913" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Euonymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euonymus aquifolium" order="Celastrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Euonymus aquifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected by E. H. Wilson in November 1908 in Washan, Sichuan. Further geographical information concerning the type locality could not be traced by the related references (such as 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson, EH" journalOrPublisher="Ltd., London" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B38" refString="Wilson, EH, 1913. A Naturalist in Western China with Vasculum, Camera, and Gun, vol. 1. Methuen &amp; Co. Ltd., London" title="A Naturalist in Western China with Vasculum, Camera, and Gun, vol. 1. Methuen &amp; Co." year="1913">Wilson 1913</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson, EH" journalOrPublisher="The Stratford Company, Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B39" refString="Wilson, EH, 1929. China: Mother of Gardens. The Stratford Company, Boston" title="China: Mother of Gardens." year="1929">1929</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, KP" journalOrPublisher="Encyclopedia of China Publishing House, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B40" refString="Yin, KP, Wang, HY, Zhong, SX, 2010. Tracing one Hundred Years of Change: Illustrating the Environmental Changes in Western China. Encyclopedia of China Publishing House, Beijing" title="Tracing one Hundred Years of Change: Illustrating the Environmental Changes in Western China." year="2010">Yin et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). Owing to the historical vicissitudes, the picture named as &quot;Wa Shan&quot; in 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson, EH" journalOrPublisher="Ltd., London" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B38" refString="Wilson, EH, 1913. A Naturalist in Western China with Vasculum, Camera, and Gun, vol. 1. Methuen &amp; Co. Ltd., London" title="A Naturalist in Western China with Vasculum, Camera, and Gun, vol. 1. Methuen &amp; Co." year="1913">Wilson (1913</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson, EH" journalOrPublisher="The Stratford Company, Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B39" refString="Wilson, EH, 1929. China: Mother of Gardens. The Stratford Company, Boston" title="China: Mother of Gardens." year="1929">1929</bibRefCitation>
) was traced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, KP" journalOrPublisher="Encyclopedia of China Publishing House, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B40" refString="Yin, KP, Wang, HY, Zhong, SX, 2010. Tracing one Hundred Years of Change: Illustrating the Environmental Changes in Western China. Encyclopedia of China Publishing House, Beijing" title="Tracing one Hundred Years of Change: Illustrating the Environmental Changes in Western China." year="2010">Yin et al. (2010</bibRefCitation>
; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Distribution map of Euonymus aquifolium Loes &amp; Rehder based on three collections." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.86180.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711040" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">5</figureCitation>
) to Jinkouhe District, Leshan City, Sichuan. A few botanists and amateurs (K. P. Yin, pers. comm.) had made attempts to find the living plants of this species around this area without result.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.86180.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711040" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Figure 5.</emphasis>
Distribution map of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loes. &amp; Rehder in Sargent" authorityYear="1913" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Euonymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euonymus aquifolium" order="Celastrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Euonymus aquifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Loes &amp; Rehder based on three collections.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Another gathering (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">P. N. Qin et al. 104</emphasis>
) identified as this species is recorded in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cheng, CY" editor="Cheng, CY" journalOrPublisher="45 (3). Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="1 - 218" refId="B4" refString="Cheng, CY, Kao, TC, Ma, QS, Ma, JS, Huang, PH, 1999. Celastraceae. In: Cheng, CY, Huang, PH, Eds., Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae vol. 45(3). Science Press, Beijing: 1 - 218" title="Celastraceae." volumeTitle="Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae vol." year="1999">Cheng et al. (1999)</bibRefCitation>
without mention of the herbarium where the specimen(s) were deposited. The collectors were a team of younger volunteers assigned by Tsofu Lu (1893-1952), the director of the then newly established Science Institute of West China, to survey in western Sichuan along the water courses in 1929 (
<bibRefCitation author="Hou, J" journalOrPublisher="Central Party Literature Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" refId="B11" refString="Hou, J, 2012. Research Institute of West China Academy of Sciences. Central Party Literature Press, Beijing" title="Research Institute of West China Academy of Sciences." year="2012">Hou 2012</bibRefCitation>
), and most of their collections include duplicates bequeathed to the present Chongqing Natural History Museum (CQNM). An extensive search at CQNM did not identify any material from this gathering (Feng Chen, pers. comm.). It is unimaginable that it lacked leaves as commented in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cheng, CY" editor="Cheng, CY" journalOrPublisher="45 (3). Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" pagination="1 - 218" refId="B4" refString="Cheng, CY, Kao, TC, Ma, QS, Ma, JS, Huang, PH, 1999. Celastraceae. In: Cheng, CY, Huang, PH, Eds., Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae vol. 45(3). Science Press, Beijing: 1 - 218" title="Celastraceae." volumeTitle="Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae vol." year="1999">Cheng et al. (1999)</bibRefCitation>
since this is an evergreen thick leathery leaved plant. Searches by enthusiastic amateurs previously and Jun 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hu’s">Hu's</normalizedToken>
team recently for living individuals near the locality of this gathering (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Distribution map of Euonymus aquifolium Loes &amp; Rehder based on three collections." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.86180.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711040" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">5</figureCitation>
) were also unsuccessful.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
We conclude that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loes. &amp; Rehder in Sargent" authorityYear="1913" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Celastraceae" genus="Euonymus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euonymus aquifolium" order="Celastrales" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aquifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Euonymus aquifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rare and vegetatively distinctive species, and this rediscovery uncovered the only presently confirmed living individuals more than 110 years after its description, which are distributed more than 100 km westward from its type locality (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Distribution map of Euonymus aquifolium Loes &amp; Rehder based on three collections." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.201.86180.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/711040" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">5</figureCitation>
). Although it is located in difficult-to-access valleys on, and living on a cliff that is unlikely to be destroyed intentionally, natural hazards might still totally damage its habitat. With just ~ 15 individuals, it should still be assessed as Critically Endangered (CR) according to the 
<bibRefCitation author="Hou, J" journalOrPublisher="Central Party Literature Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B13" refString="2022. . http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2022">IUCN (2022)</bibRefCitation>
Red List Categories and Criteria.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
